and a perfect gift if the woman in your life is looking for a new kitchen gadget. How cute are Anthropologie’s flower-embossed gardening gloves? They make us want to tend to our flowers and plants, especially with its buckle strap detailing and practical charm. For $40, mom will be happy. Anthropologie offers free shipping (typically four to eight business days), express shipping (two to three business days) for $10 and overnight shipping for $15. As one of our favorite skincare brands for eye creams and vitamin C serums, Tatcha’s Japanese ingredient-infused blend makes the ideal self-care gift. In this set, you’ll receive a cleanser, moisturizer and more. For the mom that’s constantly on-the-go, a Hydro Flask is a dynamite grab if she doesn’t already have it. It’s available in many colors, is less than $40 and built to last many years. For summertime-ready shoes, it’s worth picking up Amazon Essentials’ Two-Strapped Heel Sandal. They pair well with our favorite white dresses and work dresses alike and will soon become a wardrobe essential upon ordering. For the mom who has everything, MasterClass is a great subscription gift to learn from the pros. From Christina Aguilera’s vocal class to Gordon Ramsay’s cooking class, we love using this to sharpen our minds (and our skills). Plus, it’s one of our favorite online class platforms. Ah, we have much to thank this robot vacuum for. Not only does it make our lives easier but it truly has changed our Sunday cleaning game (much like our favorite house cleaning products). It’s one of our favorite vacuums, too. Some may say gift cards are thoughtless, but we think they’re appreciated. Choose your amount, choose your gift box and voila: your giftee will have a shopping spree to the retailer that sells practically everything. For an unbeatable work tote, Long Champ takes the cake. It’s less than $200, comes in beautiful hues and is sturdy for long commutes and overnight trips alike. Check out the New York Post Shopping sectio